      "content": "a \"goblin in the attic\"? haha. anyway, the address printing might be too slow for the real-time constraints of the ECU. \n\nif i can't use Valgrind, what are some other lighter ways to monitor the heap usage or hook into the allocator itself to see if objects are actually being deleted when remove_oldest() is called?",
